# Prod / split-stack — data host (`infra/prod/docker-compose.data.yml` MinIO + Mongo, etc.)
# Copy to **`.env`** in repo root or `docker compose --env-file` from repo root. **Never** commit a real **`.env`**.
# Secrets: `MINIO_ROOT_*`, `COTURN_LT_PASS`, and Mongo in `MONGODB_URI` if you enable auth — see `docs/prod-secrets.md`.
# Backup / restore of `mongo-data` and `minio-data`: `infra/prod/backup-restore.data.md`
#
# --- MinIO (container env; same as monolith) ---
# MINIO_ROOT_USER=minio
# MINIO_ROOT_PASSWORD=minioadmin
#
# --- How messaging-service on the APP host maps to this MinIO (S3-compatible API on :9000) ---
# S3_ENDPOINT=http://<data-private-ip-or-FQDN>:9000
#   e.g. http://10.x.x.x:9000  or  http://minio.biratbhattacharjee.com:9000  (A-record to data host; firewall: only app host)
# S3_REGION=us-east-1
# S3_BUCKET=messaging-media
# AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID=<same as MINIO_ROOT_USER on data host>
# AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY=<same as MINIO_ROOT_PASSWORD on data host>
# S3_PUBLIC_BASE_URL http(s):// origin browsers use in presigned or public URLs (often the MinIO API URL or a tunnel; align with S3_ANONYMOUS_GET_OBJECT)
# S3_ANONYMOUS_GET_OBJECT true|false  — see monolith + media docs (README / PROJECT_PLAN)
#
# Create the bucket once (e.g. from data host with mc, or first deploy script):
#   docker compose -f infra/prod/docker-compose.data.yml exec minio sh -c 'mc ...'  (after `mc alias set` — see below)
#
# --- Smoke: data host (S3 API) ---
# curl -s -o /dev/null -w "%{http_code}\n" http://127.0.0.1:9000/minio/health/live
# Console (only on this host): open http://127.0.0.1:9001 — login with MINIO_ROOT_*
# mc:  brew install minio/stable/mc  or use containerized mc against http://host.docker.internal:9000
#
# --- Smoke: app host (after messaging-service S3_* points at data MinIO) ---
# Use POST /v1/media/presign or a small script that uses the same S3 client as the service, or call service /v1/ready after deps up.
#
# --- coturn (TURN) — `turnserver.prod.template` rendered by `docker-entrypoint-coturn-prod.sh` ---
# COTURN_REALM=ekko.biratbhattacharjee.com
# Set to the data host’s public IPv4 (or split "PUBLIC/PRIVATE" in coturn docs for dual-homed); not 127.0.0.1 for real load tests.
# COTURN_EXTERNAL_IP=198.51.100.2
# Long-lived user must match the web client build (VITE) below. Password: avoid `|` (sed in entrypoint).
# COTURN_LT_USER=turn
# COTURN_LT_PASS=prod-coturn-change-me
#
# --- Web client (build on CI / app host) — `apps/web-client` / `getWebRtcIceServers()` ---
# For https://ekko.biratbhattacharjee.com use the same TURN public address as COTURN_EXTERNAL_IP (or DNS A/CNAME to it):
#   VITE_WEBRTC_TURN_URLS=turn:198.51.100.2:3478,turn:198.51.100.2:3478?transport=tcp
#   VITE_WEBRTC_TURN_USERNAME=turn
#   VITE_WEBRTC_TURN_CREDENTIAL=prod-coturn-change-me
# STUN: optional override; default includes Google’s public stun: if unset:
#   VITE_WEBRTC_STUN_URLS=stun:stun.l.google.com:19302
